org.eclipse.jetty.spdy

Interface IStream

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Callback, Stream
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    StandardStream

    public interface IStream
extends Stream, Callback

    The internal interface that represents a stream.

    IStream contains additional methods used by a SPDY implementation (and not by an application).

      • updateWindowSize

        void updateWindowSize(int delta)

        Updates the window size for this stream by the given amount, that can be positive or negative.

        Senders and recipients of data frames update the window size, respectively, with negative values and positive values.

        Parameters:
        delta - the signed amount the window size needs to be updated
        See Also:
        getWindowSize()

      • updateCloseState

        void updateCloseState(boolean close,
                    boolean local)

        A stream can be open, half closed or closed and this method updates the close state of this stream.

        If the stream is open, calling this method with a value of true puts the stream into half closed state.

        If the stream is half closed, calling this method with a value of true puts the stream into closed state.

        Parameters:
        close - whether the close state should be updated
        local - whether the close is local or remote
